    <stitle>BATTERY - BATTERY FUNCTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>BATTERY FUNCTION</title>
        <para>The three main functions of the truck battery are to:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Supply power to the starter and ignition system so engine can be cranked and started.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Supply the extra power required when the vehicle's load requirements exceed the supply from
                the charging system.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Act as a voltage stabilizer in the electrical system. The battery smooths out or reduces
                temporarily high (transient voltages) which occur in the vehicle electrical system. These excessively
                high voltages would damage other components in the electrical system if it were not for the protection
                provided by the battery.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
